document_data.History:
He joined Aniolon's exodus to found the town of [[Lliiress]], looking for a respite from the supremacy of its warrior nobility. When [[Aniolon Gruanthe]] secured the help of [[Gerinvioch]], and the dragon in turn employed the ''[[Evise Jhontil]]'' to create a barrier, Umbeso showed much curiosity about the dragon's exact doings.

The day after that, Umbeso was the first one to publicly figure out the connection between the artifact and the deaths of all who cast a spell in Lliiress.{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|175-176}} He was quick to propose leaving as a solution, before being informed that there was a barrier;{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|177}} he soon after volunteered to try a wand or other device, employing a ''[[brooch of dispelling]]'' to try and disable the ''Evise Jhontil''.

Umbeso later witnessed [[Sohj]]'s entrapment in a blinking state by the artifact corrupting his ''[[teleport]]'' spell, and Aniolon Gruanthe's final death, after the mage decided to ''[[scrying|scry]]'' on Gerinvioch.{{cite book/Realms of the Dragons II/Freedom's Promise|180}}
